up North
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adverb
Sense Number:
Definition:used as a nominal or as an adverbial phrase referring or relating to the district north of the speaker; or to specific parts of New Zealand depending on the location of the speaker:`the North Island' (by South Islanders), `Auckland' (by Wellingtonians) (cp DOWN SOUTH)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:also Far North
Pronunciation:
Notes:
